Shankar's [*Principles of Quantum Mechanics*](https://www.amazon.com/Principles-Quantum-Mechanics-R-Shankar/dp/146157675X/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0521887054&linkCode=as2&tag=axolotl0d-20&linkId=2ae25165f702314882f81af0233d11d7) is a great book, although not recommended as the first textbook for beginners. Griffiths' [*Introduction to Quantum Mechanics*](https://www.amazon.com/Introduction-Quantum-Mechanics-Pearson-International/dp/1292024089/ref=as_li_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=0521887054&linkCode=as2&tag=axolotl0d-20&linkId=2ae25165f702314882f81af0233d11d7) is much more approachable.

