### Exercise 21.1.14

Note that there is no reason why we have to use Cartesian coordinates in _parameter space_. In fact, we can also use spherical coordinates. Then we have

$$
\begin{eqnarray}
r = \sqrt{B_1^2 + B_2^2} \\
